This paper is about interpretability in machine learning, which is a topic that spans multiple sub-fields in computer science. However, given the focus on human-oriented explanations and the use of information theory, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also discusses the differences between human and machine explanations, which falls under the category of machine learning interpretability, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses natural language processing techniques to generate explanations, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language) and the paper discusses the social sciences, which falls under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
